As an old warrior I choose to lift my helmet in salute to the Vietnamese men, women and children who fought and died for their beliefs...North and South.<br><br>
In the ways of my people, Comanche and Lakota...when great warriors engage great warriors.. they lend dignity and honor to one another...even in death.<br><br>
The five wounds inflicted upon my body by gallant enemy soldiers have healed...the wounds in my heart are still bleeding.<br><br>
I would call you...&quot;Akicita was'te! -  Good soldiers!&quot;<br>
Perhaps, someday we can call each other brothers.<br><br>
I am Tatekohomni Wamble, a warrior like you!<br><br>

